\\begin{align*}
700 + \\left( 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 5 + 6 + 7 \\right) + \\left( 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 5 + 6 \\right) + \\left( 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 5 \\right) + \\left( 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 \\right) + \\left( 1 + 2 + 3 \\right) + \\left( 1 + 2 \\right) + 1
\\end{align*}

Since the sum of the first $n$ natural numbers is $n(n+1)/2$, we can calculate each of the sums in the equation. This gives
\\begin{align*}
